Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Mounting evidence there may now be community acquired disease in South Korea. Yesterday (17 Feb 2020), it was a 61-year-old woman living in Daegu, today in Seongdong-gu. Seongdong is just south of Seoul, and Daegu is 234 kms (145.4 miles) to the southeast of Seongdong (see https://www.mapsofworld.com/south-korea/cities-map.html for a map of South Korea showing cities).

There are now a number of media reports just released in South Korea mentioning a hospital has been closed to new patients in Daegu due to either "2" or "many" confirmed patients with SARS-CoV-2 infection https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20200219036751053 and https://news.joins.com/article/23709722. Clarification from knowledgeable sources would be greatly appreciated. - Mod.MPP

