[The number of countries reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 with transmission occurring outside China remains at 14 (Japan, Singapore, South Korea, Viet Nam, Malaysia, Australia, Thailand, USA, France, Germany, Spain, UK, UAE, and Egypt). There has also been local transmission noted on the cruise ship quarantined in Japan 1st identified in a quarantine officer, but continued transmission of the coronavirus has been occurring on the ship.

Please note that publications presented in these updates that come from bioRxiv are pre-peer review manuscripts, and final publications may be significantly different.

Also, it is clear that the number of reported confirmed cases differs from different reporting websites and is somewhat a function of time of day the website is updated. For example, I note the time I've accessed the Johns Hopkins website, but by the time the post is actually finished with the editing process, those numbers have at times significantly changed. Case counting is clearly a moving target and, depending upon when the website updates, the numbers may be different. - Mod.MPP]
